────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
3. UPSTREAM ATTRIBUTIONS
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

This database is built by combining the following freely available
sources. The corresponding fields on each entry carry a `source` tag so
the provenance is auditable.

  Wikidata           https://www.wikidata.org/
                     CC0 1.0 Universal (Public Domain Dedication)
                     Used for: external_ids.wikidata, titles, descriptions

  Wikipedia          https://www.wikipedia.org/
                     Multilingual: en, ja, ko, zh, fr, es, de, it, pt, ru
                     CC BY-SA 4.0
                     Used for: titles, descriptions (intro paragraphs)

  No-Intro DAT       https://datomatic.no-intro.org/
                     ROM checksums and canonical filenames are factual
                     metadata. Redistributed here under fair use; not
                     copyrightable as a database in most jurisdictions.
                     Used for: roms[]

  libretro-thumbnails https://github.com/libretro-thumbnails/
                      Thumbnail images are stored as URLs only; the
                      actual bytes remain on libretro's GitHub. Each
                      submodule keeps its own copyright statement.
                      Used for: media[].url

  romu                https://github.com/retronian/romu
  gamelist-ja         https://github.com/komagata/gamelist-ja
  skyscraper-ja       https://github.com/komagata/skyscraper-ja
                      MIT-licensed sister projects by the same author,
                      hand-curated Japanese metadata pulled in via the
                      merge_* scripts.


────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
4. SOURCES NOT USED
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

The following sources were intentionally excluded because their terms
of service or commercial licensing forbid bulk redistribution of the
returned data:

  - IGDB (Twitch Developer Services Agreement)
  - MobyGames (proprietary terms, requires a commercial agreement)
  - GameFAQs (no API, scraping disallowed)

If you contribute data to this project, please make sure it does not
originate from one of these sources.
